 The video shows two security officers arriving at the tavern to arrest a man who allegedly assaulted an employee of Highveld Emporium while walking home from work. The owner of Highveld Emporium dispatched the security company when he learnt of the assault on his employee, who was admitted to hospital with multiple injuries. Also read: UPDATE: ‘Whites’ warned to stay indoors by violent protesters, everything calm for now While trying to subdue the suspect the community rushed to his aid can be seen shoving, pulling and slapping at the two security guards.
The situation becomes explosive as more people arrive. Also read: BREAKING NEWS: One building torched in protests, businesses appealing for backup The two security guards are accused of racism and the angry community can be seen accosting the guards in the police’s presence. On Tuesday the community targeted the owner of Highveld Emporium for phoning the security guards, by looting his shop and setting it alight.
During the chaos residents of Machadodorp were warned to stay indoors and away from Potgieter Street where the shop was torched. Protesters have dispersed but police remain on alert.    Armed robbery at Auctioneers Pastor gunned down during church service Three killed in shootout with Police Suspects might be linked to seven other robberies • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za